	<body>
		<header>
			<span class="nm">kcgi</span>
			&#8212;
			<span class="nd">minimal CGI library for C</span>
			<nav>
				<span>version <span>@VERSION@</span></span>
				<span><a href="snapshots/kcgi.tgz">Sources</a></span>
				<span><a href="snapshots">Archives</a></span>
			</nav>
		</header>
		<article>
			<p>
				<span class="nm">kcgi</span> is a minimal CGI library for web applications (HTML and HTTP) in C.  
				It was designed to be simple, permissibly-licensed, and auditable.
				See a <a href="http://www.lemoda.net/c/cgi-libraries/index.html">Comparison of CGI Libraries in C</a> for
				alternatives.
				<span class="nm">kcgi</span> is a <a href="http://www.bsd.lv">BSD.lv</a> project.
			</p>
			<p>
				Some features:
			</p>
			<ul>
				<li><code>multipart/form-data</code> and <code>application/x-www-form-urlencoded</code> input</li>
				<li>lightweight functions for building HTML trees and HTTP headers</li>
				<li>simple, callback-based template system</li>
				<li>safe memory allocation functions (inspired by <a href="http://www.openssh.com">OpenSSH</a>)</li>
				<li>field (URI, form, and cookie) validation and repopulation</li>
			</ul>
			<p>
				The library itself consists of easily-auditable ISO C sources under the <a
					href="http://opensource.org/licenses/ISC" rel="license">ISC license</a>.
				The <a href="kcgi.3.html">kcgi(3)</a> manpage documents all function, variables, and usage.
				To use the library, download <a href="snapshots/kcgi.tgz">kcgi.tgz</a> and run <code>make install</code> into
				your <code>PREFIX</code> of choice.
			</p>
			<p>
				Contact <a href="http://kristaps.bsd.lv">Kristaps</a> with questions.
			</p>
			<h2>
				New in version @VERSION@...
			</h2>
			<p>
				Add a simple templating system.
				This is fully demonstrated in the <code>sample.c</code> file.
			</p>
